So I have been making a file sharing web app using Spring Boot and here is how I have facilitated getting files from the database. I will focus specifically on your problem because it is very similar to what I faced a few days ago.

Firstly, I make a POJO class `Files` which has details like `filename`, `lastmodified`, and some others which are not relevant to your problem here.

I get the files from the database using a DAO class, add the above mentioned attributes in an ArrayList and return the ArrayList back to the Controller class. In the Controller class, using `request` object I do the following: `request.setAttribute(&quot;files&quot;, files);`

Now in my jsp file, I use JSTL to get files like this:
```
&lt;c:forEach var=&quot;j&quot; items=&quot;${files}&quot;&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;
        &lt;a href=&quot;resources/files/${j.getFilename()}&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;${j.getFile()}&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/c:forEach&gt;
```

`resources/files/` is the path where my files are stored after being uploaded and using `target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;` enables me to open files (files which the browser allows to be opened such as pdf and text files) in a new tab and those which cannot be opened get automatically downloaded.

